6 Subject: Municipal and county government; municipal charters; City of
7 Rutland; amendments; approval
8 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to approve
9 amendments to the charter of the City of Rutland to limit the maximum penalty
10 for violation of an ordinance to the maximum penalties authorized under 24
11 V.S.A. § 1974, increase the tax on the grand list for purposes of replacing fire
12 equipment, establish a tax on the grand list for purposes of replacing police
13 equipment, require the City’s Purchasing Agent to make purchases based on
14 bids whenever the value of the proposed purchase exceeds the amount
15 established in the City’s Purchasing Policy, reorganize the composition of the
16 Board of Commissioners of the Rutland Redevelopment Authority, and
17 establish staggered terms for the members of Board of Commissioners of the
18 Authority.
19 An act relating to approval of amendments to the charter of the City of
20 Rutland
